Git 5/5 hygiene and mistakes

- Write good commit messages 
- One logical change per commit 
- Avoid bad commit names like “fixfixfix33”

Pre-commit automation - linters:
So we use linters & hook recommit tools into pre commits - to run checks - pass - gets committed 

- Help enforce coding standards + standards
- Catch mistakes 
- Prevent broken code to repo 
- Hook into CI pipelines for formatting + testing + scanning 

Common mistakes:
- Forgetting to start off with git pull  to get the latest changes to avoid merge conflicts 
- Force pushing commits to shared branches 
- Committing screws like .env 
- Merging w/out review 
- Not using .gitignore properly 

Common mistakes in orgs:
- Preventing secrets leak 
- Using gir.secrets , trofflehig 
- Cleaning secrets from history 
- Auditing repo contributors + log 
